So this is another interesting piece of,

00:29:32.680 --> 00:29:34.880
I don't know, a piece of the puzzle here

00:29:36.839 --> 00:29:40.560
is that some of these content items I've pulled down,

00:29:40.560 --> 00:29:43.359
I don't actually have access to.

00:29:43.359 --> 00:29:48.359
And that's because on this server, I am an administrator.

00:29:48.560 --> 00:29:51.560
So I can use Connect Widgets to pull down

00:29:51.560 --> 00:29:54.760
actually the full set of content items

00:29:54.760 --> 00:29:56.439
that exist on the server.

00:29:56.439 --> 00:29:59.079
If you're a publisher, you only get to pull down

00:29:59.079 --> 00:30:01.680
the content items that you own

00:30:01.680 --> 00:30:04.239
and that you're a collaborator on.

00:30:04.239 --> 00:30:06.839
So that's something to keep in mind

00:30:06.839 --> 00:30:09.160
as you use Connect Widgets.

00:30:09.160 --> 00:30:13.199
As an administrator, I need to be sort of more aware

00:30:14.040 --> 00:30:14.880
of this and more careful

00:30:14.880 --> 00:30:18.680
because I can produce a content item like this one

00:30:18.680 --> 00:30:23.680
where even I don't have access to view the thumbnails

00:30:24.839 --> 00:30:27.479
for each of these content types.

00:30:27.479 --> 00:30:31.160
So for this one, this is something that I know I own

00:30:31.160 --> 00:30:33.520
and it has a nice thumbnail image.

00:30:33.520 --> 00:30:34.839
I can visit it.

00:30:34.839 --> 00:30:37.319
For this one, let's see.

00:30:37.319 --> 00:30:42.319
I'm sure that Nick won't mind,

00:30:44.000 --> 00:30:45.520
but I wanted to show you,

00:30:45.520 --> 00:30:47.719
this is a feature that's been added

00:30:47.719 --> 00:30:50.079
in the last six months to Connect

00:30:50.959 --> 00:30:55.040
where we've put in a request for access workflow.

00:30:56.000 --> 00:30:59.599
So as actually an administrator,

00:31:00.439 --> 00:31:05.239
I don't have the ability to send access requests.

00:31:05.239 --> 00:31:08.439
I can just add myself to the content,

00:31:08.439 --> 00:31:11.439
but that action will be audited.

00:31:11.439 --> 00:31:13.880
So I can add myself as a viewer

00:31:13.880 --> 00:31:16.000
or a collaborator to the piece of content.

00:31:16.000 --> 00:31:19.839
If I were logged in here as a publisher,

00:31:19.839 --> 00:31:24.280
I would see these same options.

00:31:26.800 --> 00:31:30.800
I could request access as a collaborator or as a viewer,

00:31:30.800 --> 00:31:33.479
but it would send Nick an email

00:31:33.479 --> 00:31:35.599
letting him know that I had requested

00:31:35.599 --> 00:31:38.239
and asking him to give me those permissions.

00:31:39.160 --> 00:31:42.400
Similarly, for a viewer role,

00:31:42.400 --> 00:31:45.439
you only have the ability to request view access

00:31:45.439 --> 00:31:48.000
since you don't have publisher rights

00:31:48.000 --> 00:31:50.800
and it doesn't make sense for you to be a collaborator.

