00:50:17.120 --> 00:50:18.399
I skipped over this.

00:50:18.399 --> 00:50:22.600
You select your share

00:50:23.679 --> 00:50:28.120
and then it'll go in and inspect all of the directories

00:50:28.120 --> 00:50:29.879
inside of the repository

00:50:29.879 --> 00:50:33.679
for anything that contains a manifest JSON file.

00:50:33.679 --> 00:50:36.879
So everything, all of the individual content items

00:50:36.879 --> 00:50:38.800
that you put into a repository

00:50:38.800 --> 00:50:41.840
need to be sort of bundled into their own directories

00:50:41.840 --> 00:50:44.399
with their own individual manifest files.

00:50:44.399 --> 00:50:46.439
You can't just create one manifest file

00:50:46.439 --> 00:50:49.280
that covers lots of different content items

00:50:49.280 --> 00:50:51.919
and publish them all as one big group.

00:50:51.919 --> 00:50:53.159
I know that's been asked for though,

00:50:53.159 --> 00:50:56.320
but today you still have to publish

00:50:56.320 --> 00:50:58.959
individual content items as individual items

00:50:58.959 --> 00:51:00.959
with individual manifest.

