00:53:24.639 --> 00:53:26.120
And Kelly, one other question,

00:53:26.120 --> 00:53:27.520
I think maybe you answer this,

00:53:28.320 --> 00:53:30.159
but it was asked ahead of time.

00:53:30.159 --> 00:53:33.280
Will the contents be only ones that you specify

00:53:33.280 --> 00:53:35.439
in the connect widget markdown?

00:53:36.840 --> 00:53:40.080
Or is that including all published content by default?

00:53:41.040 --> 00:53:43.479
So that's a good question.

00:53:43.479 --> 00:53:47.520
I think it depends on how you, yes.

00:53:48.959 --> 00:53:51.239
The question, the answer is yes,

00:53:51.239 --> 00:53:52.800
but it depends, you have to be careful

00:53:52.800 --> 00:53:54.120
on how you write the code, right?

00:53:54.120 --> 00:53:58.399
So if I'm writing something that is

00:54:02.360 --> 00:54:07.239
one of these connect widgets that pulls all of the content

00:54:07.239 --> 00:54:11.800
and then filters by a tag like Python

00:54:11.800 --> 00:54:16.800
that includes things that other people have created

00:54:17.919 --> 00:54:20.719
that I am not in full control over

00:54:20.719 --> 00:54:23.679
and is scheduled up to run on the schedule,

00:54:24.280 --> 00:54:26.840
you could pull in content that you didn't intend to

00:54:26.840 --> 00:54:30.840
because other people can add content to that tag, right?

00:54:30.840 --> 00:54:35.360
So you're not in full control of what will end up

00:54:35.360 --> 00:54:39.399
being rendered as the content item

00:54:40.639 --> 00:54:44.080
and saved if it's running on a schedule.

00:54:44.080 --> 00:54:45.919
If you're concerned about that

00:54:45.919 --> 00:54:50.919
and you really wanna make sure that the content items

00:54:51.280 --> 00:54:53.520
that are going to appear on the page

00:54:54.360 --> 00:54:56.679
are exactly the ones you want at all times,

00:54:57.520 --> 00:55:00.879
I'd recommend either really making sure

00:55:00.879 --> 00:55:03.639
that the logic you're using to pull in

00:55:03.639 --> 00:55:07.879
that set of content items is exactly what you want it to be

00:55:07.879 --> 00:55:11.000
and other people can't throw in content

00:55:11.000 --> 00:55:13.959
into that funnel potentially,

00:55:13.959 --> 00:55:18.879
or you don't publish with the source code backed,

00:55:18.879 --> 00:55:21.399
or you don't run it on the schedule

00:55:21.399 --> 00:55:24.560
and you're just manually updating.

00:55:24.560 --> 00:55:26.600
Those are your sort of options there.

